Salary: Not for Profit Salary Packaging on offer
Ad Text:
2 years max term fulltime opportunity (with view to extend)
Flexible location across NSW, WA, VIC and TAS, with the option to work in a hybrid model
Contribute to high‑quality project delivery across a diverse and growing organisation

About the Role:

As a Business Analyst, you will work with stakeholders from all parts of BaptistCare to elicit requirements and capture business needs, to articulate and document business requirements, to conduct as-is/to-be business process mapping and business process design, to participate in project delivery through design reviews and walk-throughs, to validate and communicate outcomes.

You’ll play a pivotal role in transforming aged care through technology by supporting the selection and rollout of our new national clinical records platform across all 51 aged care homes. You’ll assess existing clinical systems, conduct market scans for alternative solutions, and evaluate applications to identify the best platform for BaptistCare. Beyond selection, you’ll be instrumental in supporting the implementation of the chosen solution, ensuring smooth integration into daily operations and delivering tangible benefits for both residents and staff. This is a unique opportunity to apply your analytical expertise, process insight, and passion for improving clinical care through innovative technology.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead structured analysis and documentation to support the selection and implementation of a national clinical records platform, reducing the risk of vendor or configuration issues.
Facilitate stakeholder engagement, capturing clinical and operational requirements, workflows, and concerns to ensure all perspectives are reflected in evaluation and design decisions.
Conduct detailed gap analysis of current clinical systems to define must-have features, ensuring the new solution meets both operational and clinical needs.
Develop evaluation criteria and assessment metrics, providing objective, transparent comparison of vendor solutions.
Analyse and document all cost components, highlighting variances and providing insights to support informed financial decision-making.
Support transition and implementation planning, clarifying priorities, sequencing, and dependencies to ensure smooth adoption across all 51 aged care homes.
Translate complex processes and data into clear, actionable insights to guide strategic decisions and optimise clinical operations.

About the Team:

The Information & Digital team drives innovation and transforms care at BaptistCare through cutting-edge technology, seamless operations, and smart risk management. You’ll join a collaborative, solutions-focused team that values creativity, flexibility, and turning complex projects into real-world impact for our frontline teams.

About You:

Minimum 5 years’ experience as a business analyst delivering complex process, data and system change initiatives.
Previous experience within healthcare and/or aged care sector or consultancy experience
Demonstrated experience working on enterprise system implementations or replacements, particularly clinical systems e.g.: (EHR, EMR solutions).
Tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Business Analysis or a related discipline.
Experience in mapping, analysing, and improving business processes using BPMN or other structured process methodologies.
Solid understanding of systems, data and integration concepts, with the ability to document application and data architectures.
Experience defining and supporting data and system migration approaches, including sequencing, dependencies and risk considerations.
High-level written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts for executives, business users and technical team
Previous experience participating on Project teams
Experience using business analysis and delivery tools such as Visio, Jira, Confluence, MS Project or equivalent.
Ability to develop relationships with key organisational stakeholders, including Execs and Business users.
Highly developed interpersonal skills and ability to work harmoniously in a team environment.

Passionate about creating impactful solutions that support those we serve? We’d love to hear from you!

About Us:

We are proud to be part of the merged care organisation that will be known nationally as BaptistCare. As a for purpose, Christian care organisation, we are committed to providing exceptional support and services across Australia.  Together with Baptcare (VIC, TAS, SA) and Baptist Care SA we employ over 12,000 dedicated employees and support over 38,000 customers to help people live well with dignity and purpose. From older Australians and their families to people facing significant disadvantage, our passion and our priority are the customers we serve. We strive to deliver care as it should be – with people right at the centre. 

We love what we do and the communities we help. With us you can deliver life transforming care, create a career you’ll love, and join a team who make a difference.

If you would like to be considered for this role, please click ‘’Apply’’ and attach your resume.

Applicants are encouraged to apply as soon as possible as applications may be reviewed prior to the closing date. Closing Date is subject to change without notice. 

Successful applications will be subject to a variety of background checks including police background check via our online police check system.

BaptistCare – Transforming lives by expressing the love of Christ.

Unsolicited candidate profiles or CVs from recruitment agencies will not be accepted. Thank you.

Location: Orange, Blue Mountains & Central West NSW
Ad Text:
Company description:



Workplace Type: Onsite

About Newmont


At Newmont, we're not just a world-leading gold and metals producer - we're a team united by our commitment to shaping a more inclusive, sustainable, and responsible mining industry. Joining us means becoming part of a global, diverse workforce where everyone is valued, empowered, and encouraged to grow. Our people are the heart of our success, bringing exceptional skill, integrity, and dedication to everything we do as an organization and we're dedicated to creating a workplace where everyone can thrive.

About Cadia


Our Cadia Valley Operation in New South Wales is situated about 25 kilometers from Orange and 250 kilometers west of Sydney. Cadia produces gold doré bars from a gravity circuit and gold-rich copper concentrates from a flotation circuit. The operation includes the Cadia East Mine which is globally renowned for its use of block caving, a large-scale underground mining method.


We acknowledge the Wiradjuri people, traditional custodians of the land surrounding Cadia, and proudly run an Indigenous Buddy Program to enrich the workplace experience our Indigenous employees. As a residential (drive-in / drive-out) mine, Cadia values community deeply, offering both financial and in-kind support to organizations across Blayney, Cabonne, and Orange townships. The Orange region is often referred to as the gateway to Country New South Wales with acclaimed wineries, fine dining, annual festivals and charming heritage villages making for an unparalleled work-life balance.

Who we're looking for

We are seeking an experienced Analyst Asset Management to play a critical role in driving cost discipline, financial transparency and reliability outcomes across our fixed plant operations. We value transferable skills and diverse backgrounds — if this role excites you, we'd love to talk.

This is a senior individual contributor role suited to someone who thrives at the intersection of engineering, financial modelling and enterprise systems—delivering accurate budgets, robust forecasts and data-driven insights that improve asset and maintenance strategies.

About the Role

Reporting to the Supervisor, you will support significant fixed-plant OPEX and CAPEX portfolios, partnering closely with Asset Management, Planning & Scheduling, Finance and site leadership.

Your work will anchor the site's cost performance through budget development, cost analytics, strategy economics, BI reporting and high-quality data governance across SAP and our work management systems.

You will grow the strategic and financial skillset of an Asset Manager while remaining an individual contributor.

Key Responsibilities:

Build and maintain detailed OPEX and CAPEX budgets and forecasts at equipment and strategy level
Deliver monthly plan-vs-actual reporting, variance analysis and unit-cost insights
Analyse key cost drivers including materials, labour, contractors and downtime, and track savings initiatives
Translate engineering analysis outcomes into financially quantified maintenance strategy improvements (NPV/IRR)
Design and maintain Power BI dashboards integrating work order, vendor, materials and budget and actuals cost data
Ensure strong SAP S/4HANA, FieldGlass and MOS/WMS data hygiene and contractor cost reconciliation
Support outage and preventative maintenance planning through accurate cost and materials alignment
Coach planners and supervisors on financial discipline, data quality and continuous improvement practices
Prepare management packs and facilitate regular cost and performance reviews with senior stakeholders

You are analytical, commercially minded and confident operating in complex operational environments. You enjoy working with large datasets, challenging assumptions and influencing decisions through clear, evidence‑based insights.

You will bring:

Tertiary qualifications in Engineering, Finance, Economics or Commerce are valued, however, we also welcome applicants from trade or maintenance backgrounds who have built strong CMMS capability, analytical skills and commercial acumen through experience and further study.
Strong experience in asset-intensive or fixed-plant environments, ideally within maintenance or reliability.
Demonstrated capability in budgeting, forecasting and cost modelling for large operations
Advanced CMMS literacy (SAP skills highly regarded), with strong Power BI and Excel skills
Experience applying strategy economics, PMO/Criticality and risk-based maintenance principles
The ability to coach and influence cross-functional stakeholders to deliver initiatives and uplift cost control and data quality improvements.
A proactive, improvement-focused mindset aligned to safety, compliance and operational excellence

Please note this is a residential role in Orange, NSW with a 5/2 (Monday to Friday) or 5/2-4/3 (9 day fortnight) work pattern.



Job description:

Unique opportunity with the Asset Management team at Cadia

Contract | Immediate Start | Adelaide (Hybrid)

An enterprise scale transformation program is underway to modernise and integrate clinical, ancillary medical and enterprise systems within a complex healthcare environment. We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to play a pivotal role within the Clinical & Ancillary workstream of this major technology transition.

This role will suit an experienced Business Analyst who is confident operating in hospital or healthcare settings and enjoys working across both business and technical teams to deliver fit-for-purpose clinical and operational solutions.

Key responsibilities include:

Leading requirements elicitation, documentation and validation across clinical, patient administration and ancillary medical systems
Analysing current-state processes and identifying opportunities for improvement and standardisation
Supporting fit-gap analysis with vendor solutions and documenting functional specifications
Working with technical teams on integration, reporting and data migration requirements
Contributing to change impact assessments, training inputs and adoption activities
Supporting UAT planning, test case development and issue resolution
Maintaining clear traceability across requirements, design decisions and deliverables
You will bring:

5+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst within large, complex environments (healthcare or hospital experience strongly preferred)
Strong understanding of clinical, patient administration and broader enterprise processes (finance, HR, procurement)
Proven experience with requirements management, fit-gap analysis and functional documentation
Confidence engaging with a wide range of stakeholders, from clinicians and operational teams through to senior leaders
Exposure to vendor-led enterprise or clinical systems (e.g. ERP, PAS, medical or hospital platforms)
Excellent communication, facilitation and analytical skills
The ability to work autonomously within a structured program environment
Engagement Details
Contract role aligned to a major transformation workstream
Immediate start available
Hybrid working arrangement (4 days onsite, 1 day remote)
Adelaide-based

Ad Text:
Hybrid work environment
Based at our Sydney CBD Head Office
Play an important part shaping the future of our iconic Australian institution

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to join the Payment Operations Program (POP) Project on a 12‑month fixed-term salaried contract.

In this role, you will be responsible for delivering high‑quality foundational gap analysis and developing effective remediation solutions to support the project's objectives.

Success in this position will require advanced communication skills and exceptional stakeholder management, supported by demonstrated experience in a similar role engaging a broad, horizontally diverse cross‑section of the bank at an enterprise level.

Your background

Deep expertise in delivering business analysis for large scale complex data migration projects.
Exceptional interpersonal skills to collaborate, influence and partner effectively with key business and technical stakeholders across the Reserve Bank.
Strong business analysis experience, knowledge and skillsets.
Experienced in understanding, gathering, and documenting complex requirements for a variety of business areas, systems and domains.
Proven track record of successful end to end project delivery experience (Agile/Waterfall) in large enterprise environments, with a focus on meeting deadlines and achieving objectives.
An energetic and strategic thinker who has a meticulous attention to detail.
Fast learner with a curious and proactive mindset-willing to drive progress and delivery proactively.


Additional requirements

Strong working knowledge of ITIL v4 frameworks and practices
Demonstrated experience in Agile and hybrid Agile/Waterfall environments, including writing user stories, acceptance criteria, and process documentation
Proficiency in process mapping and producing high-quality documentation such as service definitions, process flows, and RACI matrices
Solid understanding of system integrations and external interfaces
Strong capability to analyse data, identify key insights, and interpret their potential implications
Demonstrated capability to engage and influence enterprise‑level stakeholders through clear, credible verbal and written communication


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people.

Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go.

Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts.

We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

About us: 
Unitywater operates in one of Australia’s most exceptional environments in terms of natural beauty, geographical and demographic breadth. We operate on Kabi Kabi, Jinibara and Turrbal Country, proudly providing safe and reliable water to customers in Moreton Bay, Sunshine Coast and Noosa. We are a water utility serving one of the fastest growing regions in the country. 
We think a pretty good job starts here. 
  
About the role: 
At Unitywater, we’re shaping the future of water and wastewater services for our community and we’re looking for a Planning and Analysis Manager to help us do it.
In this pivotal role, you’ll lead and inspire a high-performing team, empowering the business with insights that matter. You’ll partner closely with senior leaders across the organisation, providing forward-looking financial planning, forecasting and analysis that directly drives business performance and investment decisions.
Your work will be at the centre of linking people, performance and strategy, making a meaningful difference to Unitywater, our customers, and our community.

As our Planning and Analysis Manager, you will:

Partner with leaders to deliver data-driven, forward-thinking insights.
Lead business unit planning including rolling forecasts, budgeting and long-range modelling.
Drive performance reporting that empowers decision-making at every level.
Inspire and grow your team to build capability and deliver impactful analysis and advice.
Champion innovation in reporting and analytics, driving automation, self-service and digital capability.
Strengthen investment governance with financial modelling and scenario planning.[SW1]
This role is more than numbers, it’s about shaping Unitywater’s strategic future, influencing decisions at the highest level, and building a culture of insight and performance.
This is your opportunity to influence, build a culture of insight and performance, and help shape a sustainable future with Unitywater. If you’re a collaborative, future-focused leader ready to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.
  
About you: 
Our One Unitywater behaviours - Create the Future, Care Together, and Own It – define how we work together at Unitywater. To contribute to this, you will demonstrate the following skills and qualities for the role: The requirements for the position are:

Professional expertise: CA/CPA qualified with strong foundations in finance, planning and performance.
Strategic partnering skills: Proven ability to influence and advise senior leaders with insight-led recommendations.
Planning excellence: Experience leading budgeting, forecasting and scenario modelling to optimise business performance.
Analytical strength: Advanced ability to deliver meaningful variance analysis, trend insights and executive-level reporting.
Systems mindset: [SW2][LJ3] A passion for leveraging technology, automation and self-service tools to enhance decision making.
Investment expertise: Strong financial modelling, evaluation and scenario planning to support business cases.
People leadership: Collaborative, engaging leader who builds capability and empowers high-performing teams.
Data integrity: Sound understanding of governance and ability to ensure accurate performance data.
Delivery focus: Detail-oriented, organised and resilient in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
  
Working at Unitywater:
As a Unitywater team member you will enjoy a range of benefits: 

Flexibility: We value flexibility and support work-life balance with hybrid and flexible working, purchased annual leave and access to floating public holidays. Tell us what this looks like for you! 
Wellbeing: We offer several initiatives to support your wellbeing, such as discounted private health insurance, salary packaging, employee assistance program, and access to retailer discounts and benefits. 
Learning and Development: We offer a range of opportunities to feed your curiosity such as: Walk on Country experience, study assistance, and access to a dedicated learning program and professional memberships. 
Extras: We invite you to join our dedicated employee networks focused on First Nations Reconciliation, LGBTIQ+, CALD, Gender, Life Stage diversity, and Accessibility.  
We celebrate, value and include people of all backgrounds, gender and expressions, sexualities, cultures, bodies and abilities. We are committed to a workforce that reflects the diversity of the community we serve and fostering a workplace that is diverse and inclusive, where you feel connected, are safe to be yourself and supported to be the best version of yourself.
We strive to have a workforce that reflects the diversity of the community we serve and encourage all suitable applicants to apply for this role. Please feel free to share your pronouns and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process. 
If you would like to speak to a team member about our commitment to diversity and inclusion, please contact our Inclusion Specialist emma.guest@unitywater.com or Reconciliation Action Plan Advisor rebecca.williams@unitywater.com.
 
Additional information: 

We are proud to be recognized as an employer of choice for women by WORK180.
We are proud members of Pride in Diversity and Australian Disability Network.  
We are a 2025 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.
  
Ready to Apply?
At Unitywater, we believe diverse experiences, perspectives and backgrounds make us stronger. If you’re passionate about shaping business performance and leading with purpose, we’d love to hear from you. Bring your skills, ideas and energy and help us create a sustainable future, together.
How to Apply
Please apply online following the links, and make sure to upload your up-to-date resume and cover letter. 
If you’re successful we will need you to undergo a few checks….  We know they might not be the fun part, but you will need to confirm your right to work in Australia and complete relevant pre-employment checks, including verification of criminal history, drivers licence and driving history, alcohol and other drug screening. 
 
Applications close:  Midnight Friday 13th February 2026 
 
For further information please contact the Talent Acquisition team at careers@unitywater.com

MinterEllison is one of Australia's largest independent law and consulting firms. With a heritage of almost 200 years, we are known for our excellence, and our authentic and enduring relationships with our clients, our people and our communities.

MinterEllison helps our clients to solve complex problems every day. We do this by our full-service legal offering and complementary advisory offering, MinterEllison Consulting, where clients seek out our industry-informed independent advisors who understand where strategy meets risk, and how to unlock opportunities.

We offer opportunities to work on industry-leading mandates for top-tier clients, while being part of a high-performing and collaborative team that values excellence, diversity of thought, curiosity, and inclusion. We value our people and empower them to achieve their ambitions - with the support, trust and autonomy to grow their careers in meaningful ways.

At MinterEllison, we're leading the way with AI and other emerging technologies, powering innovation right across our firm. You will have the opportunity to engage with AI tools we've built, and other external AI tools, to enhance efficiencies and excellence internally and with our clients.

We support sustainable ways of working regarding how, when and where you work and offer a wide range of social, financial and health benefits (see https://www.minterellison.com/-/media/Minter-Ellison/Files/Careers/MinterEllison-Employee-Benefits-Dec_2025.pdf)

The Role

The Business Systems team plays a critical role in maximising the firm's investment in Elite 3E (ERP) and other finance-specific systems (including Intapp Time) and integrations. We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to join a small team of Business Analysts. This role with contribute to the effective delivery of high-quality projects and work packages for firm-wide operational and improvement initiatives.

The Senior Business Analyst will leverage knowledge of complex transactional systems (preferably finance-related) to manage business requirements, analysis, and design outputs, working closely with the Business Analysis Manager and team managers across Operations, Support and Training, Data & Reporting, and Testing.

Key Responsibilities

Lead or participate in requirements elicitation workshops and stakeholder forums
Complete requirements analysis, including data, security, and stakeholder impact analysis
Create high-quality documentation including BRDs, functional specifications, gap analyses, and process flow diagrams
Conduct walkthroughs of Business Analysis documentation prior to handover to development teams
Assist with deployment tasks for product releases and minor upgrades
Liaise with developers, SMEs, and project team members on work items and deliverables
Assist with test planning and review test cases to ensure adequate coverage
Provide subject matter expertise in various Practice Management system areas
Maintain issues registers, defect logs, run sheets, and other project artefacts as required
Contribute to continuous improvement of Business Analysis processes with a focus on agility, responsiveness, and high-quality outcomes
Carry out other Business Analyst tasks as requested by the Business Analysis Team Manager or Head of Business Systems

Essential Requirements

Experience & Knowledge:

Sound understanding and experience in Finance/ERP and Time management systems, ideally including integrations and system dependencies (Elite 3E advantageous)
Significant experience analysing requirements and developing specifications with a focus on robust, scalable solutions
At least 5 years' experience within a complex corporate or professional services environment
Intermediate-advanced SQL knowledge and understanding of APIs/integrations
Sound understanding of ITIL principles, project delivery, and the software development lifecycle
Understanding of both Agile and Waterfall methodologies
Experience with Anti-Money Laundering (AML) implementation or strong knowledge of AML compliance processes within Finance systems
Professional services/ legal firm experience advantageous

Skills:

Strong analytical, investigative, and problem-solving capabilities
Excellent relationship-building skills with experience influencing key stakeholders at all levels
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Adaptable in meeting changing requirements and competing priorities
Effective time and task management to achieve timely delivery of project tasks





How to apply

We encourage applications from people of all ages, abilities, cultural backgrounds, genders (including trans or gender diverse), LGBTQ+ people and those with carer responsibilities. We particularly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people to apply.

We prefer to connect with people directly, so please submit your CV by clicking on the 'Apply' button. We encourage all applications, including if you do not meet all the criteria listed for the role. Your application will also enable us to consider you for other opportunities that may be available at MinterEllison.

If you are currently a MinterEllison employee, please apply through the internal careers page.

If you would like further information, require any adjustments throughout the recruitment process or for a confidential discussion, please contact Danielle.Miller@minterellison.com.

MinterEllison is one of Australia's largest independent law and consulting firms. With a heritage of almost 200 years, we are known for our excellence, and our authentic and enduring relationships with our clients, our people and our communities. Clients seek out MinterEllison to help them solve complex problems every day. We do this by our full-service legal offering and complementary consulting offering.

We offer opportunities to work on industry-leading mandates for top-tier clients, while being part of a high-performing and collaborative team that values excellence, diversity of thought, curiosity, and inclusion. We value our people and empower them to achieve their ambitions - with the support, trust and autonomy to grow their careers in meaningful ways.

At MinterEllison, we're leading the way with AI and other emerging technologies, powering innovation right across our firm. You will have the opportunity to engage with AI tools we've built, and other external AI tools, to enhance efficiencies and excellence internally and with our clients.

We support sustainable ways of working regarding how, when and where you work and offer a wide range of social, financial and health benefits (see https://www.minterellison.com/-/media/Minter-Ellison/Files/Careers/MinterEllison-Employee-Benefits-Dec_2025.pdf)

The Role

We are currently recruiting for a Senior Commercial Finance Consultant for an opportunity based in our Sydney office with hybrid working arrangements available. In this role, you will be working with the Commercial Finance team and stakeholders to understand and drive MinterEllison's business performance and key drivers. With a keen focus on analysis, forecasting, and strategic planning, you will provide critical insights that drive effective decision-making at all levels. Your leadership in financial modelling, budgeting, and performance analysis will contribute to MinterEllison's success and growth.

In this role you will have the opportunity to:

Provide proactive, analytical, client focused reporting support through delivery of reports and investigation, diagnosis and rectification of issues
Oversight of key management reporting processes including administration of individual targets used to support performance measures across the Firm
Support the Commercial Finance team across the annual budgeting and monthly forecasting processes. Analyse and interpret financial results, comparing actual performance to forecasts and identifying areas for improvement.
Provide management reporting support to Partners across the Firm and own relationships with key stakeholders to drive business strategy
Conduct detailed variance analysis to explain deviations between actual results and forecasts/budgets
Provide insightful explanations of financial performance to senior finance and relevant stakeholders
Own the creation of, and look for ways to improve, monthly management reporting requirements
Support key operational finance initiatives on Billing, WIP management, cash collection and including key month-end processes
Communicate financial concepts in a clear and understandable manner for legal professionals and lay audiences

More About You

We welcome applications from candidates who have demonstratable experience in:

Minimum of 4 years in a management reporting or business analyst role
Tertiary qualification in Accounting or Commerce and part way through or completed professional qualifications e.g. CPA/CA
Ability to provide clear, concise, and actionable financial advice to internal clients, addressing their concerns and inquiries
High level of communication, numerical and analytical skills
Advanced excel skills, well-developed Outlook, Word and PowerPoint skills
Experience in Jedox, Access/ SQL, Power BI and Elite is desirable
Exposure to professional services culture would be advantageous

​Full time, continuing position with the University of Sydney as a Senior Clarity Analyst to drive strategic decision-making by providing critical insights and recommendations based on comprehensive data analysis, ensuring the University's projects are aligned with its strategic objectives

About the opportunity

The Strategic Program Office is pivotal in executing the Sydney in 2032 strategy, contributing to our vision of becoming "a better place to work, and a place that works better." The Senior Clarity Analyst is responsible for the end-to-end functional design, configuration and development, uplift, user experience, training and reporting processes for the Clarity system. Thus, providing critical insights into portfolio performance through a well-configured and fit-for-purpose Clarity platform. The role further involves collecting, analysing, and synthesising data from portfolio projects to create comprehensive reports and dashboards for university stakeholders. In addition to supporting the Head of Program Insights, they take a proactive role in enhancing reporting capabilities through hands-on configuration and development within Clarity, implementing advanced analytical techniques, optimising reporting processes, and ensuring data accuracy and consistency across the portfolio. Through their analytical skills and attention to detail, they help deliver reliable and consistent project information, laying the groundwork for effective project governance and control. Your key responsibilities will be to:

own the configuration, development and continuous improvement of the Clarity system

ensure Clarity can support in-depth data analysis through appropriate configuration of objects, attributes, workflows and reporting structures to identify patterns, trends, and potential risks across the portfolio

ensure clear and concise reporting that facilitates understanding and decision-making at all levels of the organisation

demonstrated hands-on experience configuring and developing with Broadcom Clarity PPM, including objects, attributes, workflows, financials and reporting
bachelor's degree and/or an equivalent combination of training and experience
demonstrated experience in applying and advising on portfolio and investment management practices, supported by methodologies such asPrince2, P3M3, PMBok or equivalent
experience in designing and implementing whole-of-organisation processes that are consultative and encourage support and buy-in from diverse stakeholders
experience in stakeholder engagement with broad and diverse groups resulting in valuable stakeholder input
the ability to develop/cultivate productive relationships with internal and external stakeholders at all levels
working understanding and current knowledge of relevant aspects of the Work Health and Safety Policy and relevant legislation (including Safe Laboratory Practices for roles based in Laboratory).

About the role

As the Manager, Quantitative Modelling, you will act as the organisation’s subject matter expert for Credit Risk Stress Testing and Collective Provisioning across all BOQ Group credit portfolios. You will oversee the monitoring, reporting and interpretation of collective provisioning model outcomes, providing meaningful insights that help inform decision‑making and strengthen the Group’s overall credit risk management framework.

In this role, you will lead the delivery, maintenance and enhancement of stress testing frameworks and methodologies across credit portfolios, including the uplift of capabilities aligned to BOQ’s transition to the Internal Ratings Based (IRB) approach. You will also drive the development of innovative stress testing methodologies for emerging and evolving risk types, such as Climate Risk, ensuring the organisation maintains a forward‑looking and resilient approach to risk measurement.

As a key stakeholder across the business, you will work closely with internal teams during regulatory and ICAAP stress testing cycles, ensuring timely responses to regulatory changes and audit findings. Your ability to identify and address data quality issues will be essential to maintaining the accuracy and reliability of BOQ’s quantitative models while supporting the organisation’s broader regulatory and strategic priorities.

About you




You bring 5–8 years of experience in a similar quantitative, analytical or credit risk role, supported by strong mathematical and statistical knowledge and a postgraduate qualification in a technical discipline. You have hands‑on experience in building and interpreting mathematical or statistical models, with exposure to Credit Risk, Collective Provisions, Stress Testing, Forecasting or Capital Reporting. Your understanding of how technical modelling activities connect to broader business outcomes enables you to communicate insights clearly and influence decision‑making across diverse stakeholders.

You are confident working with relevant programming languages such as SQL, SAS, VBA, R, Python or Databricks, and you’re familiar with version control tools including Git, Bitbucket or DevOps. Your background in financial services positions you well to navigate IFRS 9, Basel frameworks and APRA prudential standards, with any direct experience in these areas considered highly desirable. Alongside your technical capability, you bring strong stakeholder engagement and project management skills, allowing you to collaborate effectively and contribute to continuous improvement within a complex risk environment.

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. Your New Role

Climate change is an essential part of AustralianSuper's ESG strategy and the Fund has made a commitment to achieve Net Zero carbon emissions by 2050 in our investment portfolio. This commitment builds on the actions AustralianSuper is currently taking to manage climate-related risks and opportunities in the Fund's portfolio and is consistent with AustralianSuper's objective of helping members achieve their best financial position in retirement.

As a result of the introduction of the Australian Sustainability Reporting Standards (ASRS), AustralianSuper's mandatory reporting requirements will significantly increase in the next two years. In addition, clearly articulating AustralianSuper's ESG strategy and ambitions in line with Australian standards is essential to bringing AustralianSuper's ESG agenda to life for Members and other stakeholders.

The Senior Analyst, Sustainability Reporting is a newly created role in the Reporting & Control team within the Finance domain, and will support the execution of AustralianSuper's existing and emerging ESG reporting obligations.

Key responsibilities will include;


Building processes and controls to enable AustralianSuper to meet existing and future ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting requirements;
Collaborating with colleagues across the Fund to gather data and contribute to the broader ESG reporting implementation project;
Validate, consolidate, enhance and analyse ESG data for both external and internal ESG reporting;
Providing information and insights to internal stakeholders and preparing responses to questions from external regulators related to ESG reporting; and
Working with the Fund's external auditor to support the audit and/or review of AustralianSuper's ESG reporting.






What You'll Need

Experience in an ESG related role with exposure to ESG strategy and framework development, transition to Net Zero, ESG due diligence, and sustainability reporting.
Strong written and oral communication skills with the ability to present ideas, perspectives and issues to management.
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to work effectively with a range of people at all levels across an organisation and external stakeholders.
Significant experience in working under pressure, setting and manage conflicting priorities and meeting specified timeframes.
Comfortable with change and working in a multidisciplinary team across a global organisation.
Prior experience in translating ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting requirements and guidance into business processes and controls
Experience in sustainable finance and reporting with exposure to financial modelling and KPI (Key performance indicators) scorecards.
Passionate about sustainability and excited about the new challenges in ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting.
Tertiary qualifications in Accounting/ Finance/ Business and/or Engineering/ Environmental science/ Sustainability/ Governance or equivalent.
Completion of CA/CPA, or equivalent (desired).

We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

About our Client
  
Our client is a specialist construction and field services organisation, delivering protective coating, asset maintenance and remediation services across large, asset-heavy environments.
  
The business operates across multiple core systems and is investing heavily in its data capability to move from fragmented reporting to a centralised, scalable analytics platform. As part of this journey is building a central Azure based data lake to support enterprise-wide reporting and core data insight.
  
About the Role   
  
This is a senior, hands-on Data Analyst role, working closely with a highly experienced Senior Data professional. 
  
The focus of the role is on data integration, ingestion and transformation, sitting between source systems and the Power BI reporting layer. This role is critical in designing and building the ETL pipelines and data flows that enable reliable, trusted reporting and overall strong architecture. 
  
The environment has limited documentation, so this role suits someone who is comfortable working hands-on, navigating ambiguity, and building strong data foundations from the ground up.
  
Key Responsibilities   

Build and maintain ETL / ELT pipelines from multiple operational systems into a central data lake.
Design and manage data integration and ingestion processes, including API-based integrations.
